Rating: 4
Oh, wow, is this ever good! I doubled the sauce recipe, with the exception of the curry, and I'm glad I did. I used 1 teaspoon Penzey's Hot Curry and one teaspoon Penzey's Sweet Curry and it was perfect. Since curry has cumulative heat, it would have been much too hot had I used all hot curry, and we love spicy. The only other changes I made were to sub ginger-garlic paste for the chopped fresh ginger, pecans for the walnuts, and golden raisins for the grapes, as my husband doesn't like them. Served in whole wheat pita, this makes a wonderful hot weather meal. Definitely a keeper!

