This is a never fail recipe. As others note, you can add anything (pecans, cucumbers, red onions, mango, etc) and you can play with the mayo/yogurt combo. I never add orange juice (which I think makes it a little watery), but increase the curry powder and mango chutney. By the way, there's a mango chutney by Silver Palate (with huge chunks of mango in it) that is amazing in this dish. We eat it all summer long!

