Rating: 3
I was nervous about making this recipe because it sounded a little weird, but yum! Definitely one to make again and again. I made the following changes based on what I had in the house: West Indian curry powder & chutney, dried ginger for the fresh and some extra red onion because I like the crunch. I also added about a 1/4 teaspoon of honey, to make up for the spiciness of this chutney compared to regular chutney. Then I added a tablespoon more yogurt, because I think I used too much chicken. The results are really outstanding - sweet, spicy and creamy.

